386→                        <div id="content">Let $\epsilon &#62;0$. Is it true that, if $k$ is sufficiently large, then\[R(G)&#62;(1-\epsilon)^kR(k)\]for every graph $G$ with chromatic number $\chi(G)=k$? <br><br>Even stronger, is there some $c&#62;0$ such that, for all large $k$, $R(G)&#62;cR(k)$ for every graph $G$ with chromatic number $\chi(G)=k$?</div>
